00:00:23.077 --> 00:00:27.716
What are you making?
Pumpkin Poriyal

00:00:35.443 --> 00:00:37.539
Ingredients required to make Pumpkin Poriyal

00:00:37.758 --> 00:00:47.010
Pumpkin, Seasoning Seeds, Fresh Grated Coconut, Onions,
 Curry Leaves, Coriander, Salt, Turmeric, Oil

00:01:00.003 --> 00:01:10.422
Heat a pan, add a cup of chopped pumpkin
and add some water to boil the pumpkin

00:01:17.007 --> 00:01:21.884
Add some salt to help cook faster

00:02:04.723 --> 00:02:09.106
Coom for 2-3 mins

00:02:24.068 --> 00:02:28.647
Take the boiled pumpkin into a bowl

00:02:34.846 --> 00:02:50.425
Heat some oil in a pan, add some mustard &amp; cumin,
some white lentils, dry red chillies (4-5)

00:03:10.965 --> 00:03:17.533
Add a cup of chopped onions and 
fry til they become light brown in color

00:03:27.454 --> 00:03:31.650
Add the boiled pumpkin pieces

00:03:55.193 --> 00:04:05.120
Add a pinch of turmeric and
some salt for taste

00:04:16.394 --> 00:04:21.038
Finally, add some curry leaves

00:04:33.403 --> 00:04:38.001
Turn off the stove and take the curry
into a serving plate

00:04:41.714 --> 00:04:47.770
Top the curry with some freshly grated coconut

00:04:48.834 --> 00:04:51.871
Garnish with some coriander

